<html t:type="layout" title="Hi/Lo Guess"
  xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_3.xsd">
 
<div id="defaultMenu">
	<div id="faq">
		<h2>What is the purpose of this site?</h2>
		The purpose of this site is to have a large database of movies where users can search for a particular movie or search for something to watch based on
		site recommendations or through the community tools (articles, user recommendations, etc).
		<br/>
		<br/>
		<hr/>
		<h2>F.A.Q. (Frequently Asked Questions)</h2>
		<hr/>
		<h3>Do you have any web services that my application can use?</h3>
		Yes, we have a web service for movie information recovery from our database. If you want to use
		our movies database then you can use this web service, you will have access to standard movie information 
		like title, description, release date. Also, you will have access other properties like movie score (average score
		from the users of our site)
		<hr/>
		<h3>How can I use the web services?</h3>
		There are three possible ways to use our web service.<br/>
		<lu>
			<li>Retrieve the complete movie list: <b>http://localhost:8080/recomendar/webapi/movies/</b></li>
			<li>Retrieve one particular movie, using ID property: <b>http://localhost:8080/recomendar/webapi/movies/{id}</b></li>
			<li>Retrieve movies whose title contains a set of keys (words): <b>http://localhost:8080/recomendar/webapi/movies/{keys}.</b> Example: {keys} = toy+story</li>
		</lu>
		<br/>
		Note: Each one of these links return a XML document.
	</div>
</div>

</html>